---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const articleSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Stunning Fan-Made 2026 Logos by LogoDiffusion.ai",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "hammaadworks"
  },
  "datePublished": "2026-06-25",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "cupcal"
  }
};
---

<BaseLayout title="Stunning Fan-Made 2026 Logos by LogoDiffusion.ai" description="How LogoDiffusion.ai created the beautiful fan-made logos we use for the 2026 host countries.">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-20 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl relative z-20">
      <a href="/blog" class="text-blue-700 hover:text-black mb-8 inline-block font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-sm border-[2px] border-blue-700 hover:border-black px-4 py-2 rounded-full transition-colors">← All Guides</a>
      
      <article class="prose prose-lg lg:prose-xl max-w-none prose-headings:font-black prose-headings:tracking-tight prose-a:text-blue-700">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-outfit text-black mb-6 leading-tight uppercase">
          Stunning Fan-Made 2026 Logos by LogoDiffusion.ai
        </h1>
        
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-500 mb-12 font-medium border-b-[3px] border-black pb-6 uppercase font-outfit tracking-widest">
          <span>By hammaadworks</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>June 25, 2026</span>
        </div>

        <p class="lead text-2xl text-black font-medium border-l-[4px] border-blue-600 pl-4">
          Since we can't use the official 2026 FIFA logos, we've opted for something even better: stunning, fan-created AI designs.
        </p>

        <p class="text-black font-medium">
          If you've noticed the incredible logos representing Canada, Mexico, and the USA across CupCal, you might be wondering where they came from. They aren't the official branding—instead, they are brilliant, fan-made concepts created by the talented folks at <strong>LogoDiffusion.ai</strong>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl text-black mt-12 mb-6 font-outfit uppercase tracking-widest">The Inspiration</h2>
        <p class="text-black font-medium">
          The official branding for 2026 took a very minimalist approach, which left many fans wanting something that felt more representative of the rich cultures of the three host nations. LogoDiffusion.ai stepped up to the plate, using their AI tools to generate concepts that capture the soul of each country.
        </p>
        
        <p class="text-black font-medium">
          You can check out their entire creative process and the stunning results in their viral YouTube short:
        </p>
        
        <div class="my-8 border-[4px] border-black shadow-[8px_8px_0px_#F7803C] rounded-xl overflow-hidden aspect-[9/16] max-w-[350px] mx-auto bg-black">
          <iframe width="100%" height="100%" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/uoqpufc1Dt0" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl text-black mt-12 mb-6 font-outfit uppercase tracking-widest">Why We Use Them</h2>
        <p class="text-black font-medium">
          As a fan-made, independent schedule app, CupCal is all about celebrating the culture of the sport without the corporate red tape. We couldn't use official FIFA trademarks, but honestly, we wouldn't want to when community artwork looks this good. 
        </p>
        <p class="text-black font-medium">
          The designs for Canada, Mexico, and the USA perfectly match the bold, vibrant aesthetic of CupCal. 
        </p>

        <div class="mt-16 p-8 bg-yellow-300 border-[4px] border-black rounded-3xl shadow-[6px_6px_0px_#2E0D23]">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-outfit uppercase tracking-widest text-black mb-4">
            Shoutout to LogoDiffusion.ai
          </h3>
          <p class="text-black font-bold mb-0">
            Massive props to the creators. If you need AI-generated logos or just want to see some incredible design work, make sure to check out <a href="https://logodiffusion.ai" class="underline hover:text-blue-700 transition-colors">LogoDiffusion.ai</a> and drop a like on their video!
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(articleSchema)} />
</BaseLayout>
